&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;VP, Payments Risk &amp;amp; Compliance&lt;br&gt;Orlando, FL&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full-time&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an entrepreneurial, execution-focused VP of Payments Risk &amp;amp; Compliance to lead the design, implementation, and scaling of Modulr’s US risk and compliance framework. This is a foundational leadership role in our US expansion, reporting into the US Managing Director and working closely with UK Risk, Compliance, Product, and Engineering teams. Serves as the senior US AML and payments risk lead, responsible for overseeing the design and effectiveness of Modulr’s US BSA/AML program in alignment with sponsor bank requirements. and maintains independent escalation authority to the US Board and sponsor bank compliance leadership&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for building a sponsor-bank-aligned risk and compliance structure to support our US launch and future scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Now expanding into the US, Modulr has launched the same programmable, API-first infrastructure across ACH, RTP, FedNow, and push-to-card networks in partnership with leading sponsor banks and FIS. Our focus is high-frequency, business-critical payment flows across payroll, lending, earned wage access, and platform ecosystems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;By combining regulatory oversight, operational resilience, and modern payment connectivity, Modulr helps customers move money faster, reduce manual processes, improve liquidity visibility, and create differentiated financial experiences. The result is a trusted execution layer for embedded finance in both established European markets and the growing US opportunity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build and Lead the US Risk &amp;amp; Compliance Function&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement and manage the US risk and compliance framework aligned to sponsor bank requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate UK and EU regulatory center of excellence practices into a US-ready operating model&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish CDD, KYC/KYB, transaction monitoring, sanctions screening, and AML controls in collaboration with the sponsor bank&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain policies, procedures, and governance documentation required for US operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sponsor Bank and Regulatory Partnership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as primary US risk liaison with sponsor bank compliance, BSA/AML, and risk teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure alignment with bank-defined policies, thresholds, reporting obligations, and oversight requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support regulatory inquiries, audits, and periodic bank reviews&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensures US operations are structured and conducted in compliance with applicable federal and state regulatory requirements, including ongoing assessment of licensing obligations and regulatory perimeter considerations such as Money Transmitter Laws.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Payments Risk Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee payment scheme compliance across ACH, RTP, FedNow, and card rails&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement existing global fraud prevention tools and frameworks with risk controls across account-to-account and embedded payments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define transaction limits, monitoring thresholds, and escalation processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure operational resilience and adherence to network and sponsor-bank rules&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operational Leadership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and scale the US risk and compliance team as hiring cadence increases&lt;/li&gt;
